            "text": "I don&#x27;t generally mind a company having a standard typography as part of its public image. But it irks me that Qualcomm&#x27;s website delivers webfonts to ensure that every &quot;Q&quot; that appears anywhere on their site is rendered as their logo, even in body text where their logo is a significant distraction and harm to readability.",
